{%- comment -%}
  This should be the source of truth for the product title.
  So instead of using {{ product.title }} directly in the template,
  you should use this snippet.

  If you have a logic that modifies the product title,
  for example, splitting the original title by the first pipe character (|),
  and removing the last part, you should do it here.

  This snippet should NOT contain any styling/wrappers like <h1>, <h2>, <div class> etc.
  The styling and wrappers should be in the parent template/snippet where this snippet is rendered.

  The non-html characters should be escaped to be ready for rendering.

  Accepts:
  - product: {Object} Shopify product
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign product_title = product.title
  echo product_title | escape
-%}
